        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued November 8 at 11:27PM EST by NWS Northern Indiana</headline>
        <description>Periods of light to moderate snow are expected tonight. NWS
Northern Indiana already received several snow accumulation
reports ranging from a dusting of snow to around 1 inch (New
Buffalo, MI). Additional minor accumulations are expected,
especially on grassy or elevated surfaces. It's possible that snow
changes back rain or a mix, which will limit accumulation.

If travelling, be prepared for reduced visibility with slick and
slushy roads.

Reports of accumulations are appreciated.
</description>
